><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 04, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104mid1707825339751.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mid1707825339751.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mid1707825339751.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"tfb1665702551181\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Define a Global Constant\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Global constants must be defined in an IncludeScript called <code class=\"ph codeph\">DEFPARAM</code>.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"tfb1665702551181__context_w2755ab1b5b1_w2756ab1b5_w2757ab1\">\n<div class=\"div prereq\" id=\"tfb1665702551181__topic_d14891e1_d14892e1_d14893e1\">You must have created a project to contain your\n\t\tapplication definitions. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hkq1665702549855.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hkq1665702549855.html\" title=\"Use the Project Editor to create new Main Development Objects, add existing objects to the Project, and compile all objects referenced by the Project, and perform other project-level actions.\">Working with Projects</a>.\n                           </div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"tfb1665702551181__li_d7205e1_d7206e1_d7207e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"tfb1665702551181__p_d14894e1_d14895e1_d14896e1\">Create a new IncludeScript Library or open an\n               existing library. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ajc1665702551017.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ajc1665702551017.html\" title=\"To create IncludeScripts, Global ProcScripts, and snippets for use during modeling and construction, you use the Project Editor.\">Create a Library</a>. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">For example, to create a global constant for all your Uniface applications, create\n               or open the <code class=\"ph codeph\">SYSTEM_LIBRARY</code>. </div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"tfb1665702551181__li_d7208e1_d7209e1_d7210e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"tfb1665702551181__p_d14897e1_d14898e1_d14899e1\">Select an IncludeScript template and insert it\n               template into the library structure. The default IncludeScript is called\n                  <code class=\"ph codeph\">Empty include</code>. </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"tfb1665702551181__li_d7211e1_d7212e1_d7213e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"tfb1665702551181__p_d14900e1_d14901e1_d14902e1\">Rename the IncludeScript to\n                  <code class=\"ph codeph\">DEFPARAM</code> and change the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Description</span> to\n               something like <code class=\"ph codeph\">Global constants</code>. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">DEFPARAM</code> is a reserved name that is used only for global constant\n                  declarations.</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"tfb1665702551181__fig_d14903e1_d14904e1_d14905e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"tfb1665702551181__fig_w2758ab1b5b3b5b3b1b1b1_w2759ab1b5b3b5b3b1b1_w2760ab1b5b3b5b3b1_w2761ab1b5b3b5b3_w2762ab1b5b3b5_w2763ab1b5b3_w2764ab1b5_w2765ab1\">\n<img alt=\"DEFPARM IncludeScript defined in library\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/defparam.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"tfb1665702551181__li_d7214e1_d7215e1_d7216e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Write Script</span> to go to the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Write Script</span> worksheet, and select the <code class=\"ph codeph\">DEFPARAM</code> IncludeScript.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"tfb1665702551181__li_d7217e1_d7218e1_d7219e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"tfb1665702551181__p_d14906e1_d14907e1_d14908e1\">Declare the constant using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">#define</span> command.\n For example:</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">#define Product = \"Uniface\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qzg1665702620270.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Constants</a><p>A constant is a value that remains unchanged during the course of code execution.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_6107833\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_6107833\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Define a Global Constant Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 04, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Define a Global Constant Global constants must be defined in an IncludeScript called DEFPARAM . You must have created a project to contain your application definitions. For more information, see Working with Projects . Create a new IncludeScript Library or open an existing library. For more information, see Create a Library . For example, to create a global constant for all your Uniface applications, create or open the SYSTEM_LIBRARY . Select an IncludeScript template and insert it template into the library structure. The default IncludeScript is called Empty include . Rename the IncludeScript to DEFPARAM and change the Description to something like Global constants . DEFPARAM is a reserved name that is used only for global constant declarations. Click Write Script to go to the Write Script worksheet, and select the DEFPARAM IncludeScript. Declare the constant using the #define command. For example: #define Product = \"Uniface\" Copy Related Links Constants A constant is a value that remains unchanged during the course of code execution. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}